{"parse":{"title":"nuts","pageid":75293,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|NUTS}}\n==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/nʌts/}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-nuts.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌts|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|en|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|en|nut}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|ja|ナッツ|bor=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|p}}\n\n# {{lb|en|slang}} The [[testicles]].\n# {{lb|en|poker}} An [[unbeatable]] hand; the best poker hand available.\n#: {{ux|en|If the board is 237QA, all of spades, the '''nuts''' is 45 of spades.}}\n#: {{ux|en|If the board is 4444J, the '''nuts''' is any hand with an ace.}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{sense|poker}} {{l|en|nutted}}\n\n===Adjective===\n{{en-adj}}\n\n# {{lb|en|colloquial}} [[insane|Insane]], [[mad]].\n#: {{ux|en|After living on the island alone for five years, he eventually went '''nuts'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|Are you '''nuts?'''}}\n#: {{ux|en|Seriously? This is '''nuts!'''}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial}} [[crazy|Crazy]], [[mad]]; unusually [[pleased]] or, alternatively, [[angered]].\n#: {{ux|en|I just go '''nuts''' over her fantastic desserts.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The referee made a bad call against the home team and the crowd went '''nuts'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial}} Very [[fond]] of (''on'') someone.\n#: {{ux|en|He's been '''nuts''' on her since the day they met.}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|en|nutty}}\n* See also [[Thesaurus:insane]]\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|insane}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|boig}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|gek}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|cinglé}}, {{t+|fr|dingue}}\n* German: {{t+|de|verrückt}}, {{t+|de|irre}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|τρελός|m}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|pazzo}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|чукнат|m}}, {{t|mk|штракнат|m}}, {{t|mk|одлепен|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|loco}}, {{t+|es|zumbado}} {{qualifier|colloquial}}, {{t+|es|sonado}}, {{t+|es|tocado}}, {{t|es|tocado del ala}}, {{t|es|majareta}}, {{t+|es|chaveta}}, {{t+|es|tarambana}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|knäpp}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|crazy, pleased}}\n* German: {{t+|de|verrückt}}, {{t+|de|scharf}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|angered}}\n* German: {{t+|de|wild}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|very fond}}\n* German: {{t+|de|verrückt}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{n-g|Indicates [[annoyance]], [[anger]], or [[disappointment]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Nuts!''' They didn't even listen to what I had to say.}}\n# {{n-g|Signifies [[rejection]] of a proposal or idea, as in {{m|en|forget it}}, {{m|en|no way}}, or {{m|en|nothing doing}}; often followed by {{m|en|to}}.}}\n#: {{ux|en|They want me to pay $5 for a banana? '''Nuts''' to that!}}\n#* {{quote-web|en|author=Dan Shive|title=Comic for Monday, Mar 19, 2018|url=https://www.egscomics.com/comic/2018-03-19|work=El Goonish Shive|date=19 March 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220507025312/https://www.egscomics.com/comic/2018-03-19|archivedate=7 May 2022|accessdate=6 May 2022|text=<p>Early plans for this storyline didn't have Ellen get to fight back against Sirleck. She was just a host for Sirleck, and didn't have any agency to speak of.</p><p>Later on, I decided \"'''nuts''' to that\".</p><p>Granted, Ellen's not literally holding Sirleck back like that. Technically, the real Sirleck doesn't even have arms. This is a visual comic, however, so darn it, let's get metaphorical about it.</p>}}\n#* {{quote-web |en |date=2022-04-19 |accessdate=2022-04-19 |work=w:The Guardian |title=US supreme court rules against air force officer who refused Covid vaccine |author=Lauren Aratani |publisher=w:Guardian Media Group |text=<p>Upon denial of his exemption request, Dunn sent to a major general “a one-word memorandum that simply read: ‘'''NUTS'''!’”.</p><p>Prelogar noted that while Dunn maintains he meant no disrespect, “'''NUTS'''!” has a “well-known ‘military historical connotation’”.</p><p>She cited the case of Anthony McAuliffe, a key US military officer in the second world war who responded to a German message requesting American surrender with the one-worded answer. The American officer who delivered McAuliffe’s message to German officers clarified that, “If you don’t understand what ‘'''nuts'''’ means, in plain English, it is the same as ‘Go to hell.’”</p>}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* The association with {{m|en|testicles}} (See [[#Noun|noun above]].) adds an intensifying effect to the anger or rejection.\n* Use of \"Nuts\" rather than another form of \"No\" is often intentionally insulting. (e.g. [[w:Anthony_McAuliffe#World_War_II|Gen. Anthony McAuliffe's response to a German request for surrender]] during the Battle of the Bulge)\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|en|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|en|nut||s-verb-form}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|bugnuts|fucknuts|fuzznuts|numbnuts|nutso|nutsy|nutzoid|shitnuts\n|drive someone nuts|go nuts|nuts to}}\n\n===See also===\n* [[dead-nuts]] {{i|possibly etymologically related, but Wiktionary isn't sure about the etymology of the term}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=nstu|Unst|stun|tsun|tuns}}\n\n{{C|en|Genitalia}}"}}